
SSH Pre-Requisites

			1. install software package  name 
			2. service : sshd 
			3. daemon : sshd
			4. port : 22 
			5. configuration file : /etc/ssh/sshd_config 

	

1. Software Package
    Server: `openssh-server` (provides `sshd`)
    Client: `openssh-client` (provides `ssh`, `scp`, `sftp`)

2. Service / Daemon
    Daemon name: `sshd`
    Must be installed, running, and enabled on the server

3. Network / Port
    TCP port 22 must be open
    Accessible from the client machine

4. Configuration File
    `/etc/ssh/sshd_config` for server settings
    `/etc/ssh/ssh_config` for client defaults

5. Authentication
    User account on the server
    Password or public/private key pair (recommended)

6. Firewall / Security Rules
    Server firewall must allow port 22/TCP
    Cloud Security Groups / NSGs must permit SSH

7. System Requirements
    Linux/Unix-based OS on the server
    TCP/IP networking enabled

 Optional / Best Practices
 ========================
 Use key-based authentication instead of passwords
 Disable root login (`PermitRootLogin no`) for security
 Enable logging and monitoring for auditing
